  "text": "Most people have no idea football boots are being flipped for profit every single week. Here's how it actually works. Someone buys a limited Adidas Predator Elite at retail, let's say \u00a3200. Two weeks later, it's listed on StockX for \u00a3310. After fees, that's a clean \u00a380 profit in 14 days. The reason it works is simple, Nike, Adidas and Mizuna release limited colourways in batches of under 500 pairs. They sell out in under 20 minutes. Demand stays high. Supply doesn't come back. That gap is where the profit lives. And right now the market is moving fast, boots we track this week are already up 25 to 40%. This is exactly what we break down inside FUTICULTURE HQ every single week. Link in bio.",
